Hermes of the Ways

O happy and winning light,
From the mountain streams,
Hasten bright over the headers:
The gnarled bark of pine.

Speak to my heart,
Wind of the meadow, echo of trees:
With wilder weeds,
Teach me the secret runes
Of the leaf and the rose.

